msg.content:
The four oldest universities in the Ivy League are Harvard University, Yale, the University of Pennsylvania, and Princeton University. 

Harvard University, founded in 1636, is the oldest institution and currently has Alan Garber as their provost. 

Yale, established in 1701, is the second oldest and Scott Strobel serves as the current provost. 

The University of Pennsylvania, founded in 1740, has Wendy Raymond as its provost. 

Finally, Princeton University, established in 1746, has Debora Prentice as its provost.
